#### 🟡 MEDIUM — Exception Handling in Test
**File:** `OrderProcessorTests.cs` · **Method:** `ProcessOrder_EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError` (lines 110–118)

```csharp
try {
    processor.ProcessOrder(order);
    Assert.Fail("Expected an exception but none was thrown");
} catch (ValidationException ex) {
    Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
}
```

**Problem:** Verbose and error-prone — forgetting `Assert.Fail` silently passes. Also catches the wrong type without re-throwing if a different exception occurs.

**Fix:** Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (as you already do in the clean test):

```csharp
var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ValidationException>(
    () => processor.ProcessOrder(order));
Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
```

