### 4. Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Risk if left unchanged |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | False confidence — broken code passes silently |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Untested branch hides regressions |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | Flaky CI + 2 s wasted per run |
| 4 | Mystery Guest | Test fails on every machine except the author's |
| 5 | Exception Handling | Forgetting `Assert.Fail` silently passes |
| 6 | Eager Test | Failures are expensive to diagnose |
| 7 | Magic Numbers | Impossible to verify expected values without running code |
| 8 | Sensitive Equality | Locale/format changes cause false failures |
| 9 | General Fixture | Minor noise; remove when convenient |

Start with items 1–4 — they represent false-confidence and flakiness risks. The medium-severity items are readability/maintenance issues that can be addressed in a second pass.
